        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2579443446" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13131107522349253367">Who would think a book about four people who contemplate suicide on New Year&apos;s Eve would be funny? It is. They all show up on the same rooftop and decide not to jump, although they&apos;re not quite sure what to do once they&apos;ve made that decision. Hornby gives us four wildly different first person narratives and we go on their journey of discovery together. Especially hilarious is the character Jess, a foul-mouthed, maddening, infuriating and ultimately lovable teenager. This is a delightful and quir</span>
  <span id="freeText13131107522349253367" style="display:none">Who would think a book about four people who contemplate suicide on New Year's Eve would be funny? It is. They all show up on the same rooftop and decide not to jump, although they're not quite sure what to do once they've made that decision. Hornby gives us four wildly different first person narratives and we go on their journey of discovery together. Especially hilarious is the character Jess, a foul-mouthed, maddening, infuriating and ultimately lovable teenager. This is a delightful and quirky book and I loved it. </span>
